                    <p> Hillary Clinton called on Congress to pass the Federal Equality Act and vowed to make LGBT rights a top priority as president in a speech Saturday to a prominent gay rights organization. </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> &quot;I see the injustices and the dangers that you and your families still face and I'm running for president to end them once and for all,&quot; Clinton said at a Human Rights Campaign breakfast in Washington D.C. </p>
                
              
              
              
                  <figure class="img_half">
                    <noscript><img class="img-responsive img_inline" src="http://media3.s-nbcnews.com/j/newscms/2015_40/1247931/hillary-clinton-ejo-100315_f587d2e5b2887d5ecc5ffe2e503d363d.nbcnews-fp-360-360.jpg" alt="Image: Democratic presidential candidate Clinton speaks to supporters at the Human Rights Campaign in Washington" title="Image: Democratic presidential candidate Clinton speaks to supporters at the Human Rights Campaign in Washington" itemprop="image"/></noscript>
                    <a href="http://media3.s-nbcnews.com/j/newscms/2015_40/1247931/hillary-clinton-ejo-100315_f587d2e5b2887d5ecc5ffe2e503d363d.nbcnews-ux-2880-1000.jpg" class="js-lightbox lightbox_link">
                      <button class="btn btn_overlay"><i class="fa fa-expand"></i></button>
                      <img class="js-lazy img-responsive img_inline" src="//sslnodeassets.nbcnews.com/images/transparent-placeholder.gif" data-original="http://media3.s-nbcnews.com/j/newscms/2015_40/1247931/hillary-clinton-ejo-100315_f587d2e5b2887d5ecc5ffe2e503d363d.nbcnews-ux-320-320.jpg" alt="Image: Democratic presidential candidate Clinton speaks to supporters at the Human Rights Campaign in Washington" title="Image: Democratic presidential candidate Clinton speaks to supporters at the Human Rights Campaign in Washington"/>
                    </a>
                    <div class="js-caption_wrapper">
                      <figcaption class="img-caption img-caption_default no-margin-bottom"><span class="img-caption_txt">Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Clinton speaks to supporters at the Human Rights Campaign Breakfast in Washington on Oct. 3, 2015.</span> <i class="fa fa-camera" aria-hidden="true"></i>JOSHUA ROBERTS / Reuters</figcaption>
                    </div>
                  </figure>
                
              
                    <div class="ad-container ad-container_default ad-container_mobile ad-hide">
                      <div class="ad-label ad-hide">
                      	<a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/id/31066137/media-kit/" target="_blank">advertisement</a>
                      </div>
                      <div class="ad-content ad-xs box1" data-placement="box1"></div>
                    </div>
              
              
                    <p> The Democratic front-runner has had an evolving view on same-sex marriage and alluded to past stances in her remarks. </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> &quot;You've helped change a lot of minds, including mine, and I am personally very grateful for that,&quot; she said, adding that there's no one she'd rather share her initials with than HRC. </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> Clinton pledged to upgrade the service records of LGBT members of the military who were dishonorably discharged, and promised to fight for the rights of the transgender community facing a &quot;growing crisis&quot; of violence. She called the current law banning transgender people from serving in the military &quot;outdated.&quot; </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> &quot;We need to say in one voice that transgender people are valued. They are loved. They are us,&quot; Clinton told the crowd of 800 grassroots leaders. </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> Clinton supports the Federal Equality Act, which would update the Civil Rights Act of 1964 to protect LGBT people. </p>
                
              
                    <div class="ad-container ad-container_default ad-container_mobile ad-hide">
                      <div class="ad-label ad-hide">
                      	<a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/id/31066137/media-kit/" target="_blank">advertisement</a>
                      </div>
                      <div class="ad-content ad-xs box2" data-placement="box2"></div>
                    </div>
              
              
                
              
              
              
                
                    <div class="widget widget_tweet"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">HRC takes stage with <a href="https://twitter.com/HRC">@HRC</a> president <a href="https://twitter.com/ChadHGriffin">@ChadHGriffin</a>, who says she told him &quot;you know, I was the first HRC in your life&quot; <a href="http://t.co/VXkDr8vqLA">pic.twitter.com/VXkDr8vqLA</a></p>— Monica Alba (@AlbaMonica) <a href="https://twitter.com/AlbaMonica/status/650309493675442176">October 3, 2015</a></blockquote> <script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
              
              
              
                    <p> The former secretary of state also called out Republican candidates Ben Carson and Ted Cruz for their positions on marriage equality. </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> &quot;Ted Cruz slammed a political opponent for marching in a pride parade,&quot; Clinton said. &quot;He clearly has no idea what he's missing.&quot; </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> Those parades are &quot;so much fun,&quot; she added. </p>
                
              
                    <div class="ad-container ad-container_default ad-container_mobile ad-hide">
                      <div class="ad-label ad-hide">
                      	<a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/id/31066137/media-kit/" target="_blank">advertisement</a>
                      </div>
                      <div class="ad-content ad-xs box3" data-placement="box3"></div>
                    </div>
              
              
                    <p> <strong>Related:</strong> <a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/meet-the-press/first-read-make-or-break-month-hillary-clinton-n436801">First Read:A Make-or-Break Month for Hillary Clinton</a> </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> Clinton also alluded to controversial <a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/kentucky-governor-clerk-davis-statements-show-absurdity-n436281">Kentucky county clerk Kim Davis</a>, though she did not mention her by name. She criticized public officials for &quot;celebrating a county clerk who is breaking the law by denying other Americans their constitutional rights.&quot; </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> Clinton said she thinks about LGBT rights every day on the campaign trail and is &quot;just getting warmed up.&quot; </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> HRC president Chad Griffin called Clinton a &quot;true trailblazer and real champion for equality.&quot; HRC has not endorsed a candidate in the 2016 election yet. </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> The organization was hoping Clinton might headline their national dinner Saturday, but a spokesperson said Clinton had a scheduling conflict. She's set to make an appearance on Saturday Night Live's season premiere in New York. </p>
                
              
                    <div class="ad-container ad-container_default ad-container_mobile ad-hide">
                      <div class="ad-label ad-hide">
                      	<a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/id/31066137/media-kit/" target="_blank">advertisement</a>
                      </div>
                      <div class="ad-content ad-xs box4" data-placement="box4"></div>
                    </div>
              
              
                    <p> Vice President Joe Biden will be delivering keynote remarks instead. &quot;We're just happy to have them both,&quot; an HRC spokesperson said. </p>
                
              
              
              
              </div>
            </div>
